author: PATRICK ONEILL
title: RIVERSIDE: Driver killed in rollover crash on 91 Freeway
text:
BY PATRICK ONEILL 4, 2015 Updated: 3:12 p.m. RIVERSIDE: Driver killed in rollover crash on 91 Freeway Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» The driver of a vehicle described by one witness as a monster truck was killed Sunday, Oct. 4, after being ejected during a crash on the 91 Freeway near the Adams Street exit in Riverside.
The crash was reported at 12:52 p.m. on the westbound side of the freeway. A witness told authorities that the driver attempted to pass a car, overcompensated and overturned, according to a California Highway Patrol incident log.
The victim ended up bleeding on the ground and the truck caught fire, witnesses said. The Riverside Fire Department was called out to the scene.
The victim died at the scene. His or her name has not been released.
A light pole was knocked over during the crash. Traffic in the area was backed up for more than an hour while investigators collected evidence and worked to clean up the scene.
